qas.question: In what century did the Middle Ages begin?
What century saw the end of the Middle Ages?
What event marked the beginning of the Middle Ages?

answers.text: the collapse of the Western Roman Empire

qas.question: Along with the Renaissance, what era occurred at the end of the Middle Ages?
What is the first period of the three that Western history is traditionally divided into?

context: In European history, the Middle Ages or medieval period lasted from the <a0_0>5th<a0_0/> to the <a1_0>15th<a1_0/> century. It began with <a2_0>the collapse of the Western Roman Empire<a2_0/> and merged into the Renaissance and the <a3_0>Age of Discovery<a3_0/>. The Middle Ages is the middle period of the three traditional divisions of Western history: <a4_0>Antiquity<a4_0/>, Medieval period, and Modern period. The Medieval period is itself subdivided into the Early, the High, and the Late Middle Ages.
